mountblockd
===========

This is Launch Daemon blocking volumes specified in `<ProgramArguments>` of `com.nanoant.mountblockd.plist`.

Based on original code published at:
[superuser.com](http://superuser.com/questions/336455/mac-lion-fstab-is-deprecated-so-what-replaces-it-to-prevent-a-partition-from-m/336474#336474)


Installation
------------

1. put volume names you want to block in `<ProgramArguments>` of `com.nanoant.mountblockd.plist`.
2. `make`
3. `sudo make install`
4. `sudo make start`


